Job duties: You will assist in managing and coordinating day-to-day site activities to ensure smooth and efficient operation of local projects. You will be responsible to liaise between main contractors, architect/consultants, utilities suppliers and clients on project coordination and construction programme issues.

Requirements

Degree or Higher Diploma in Building Services or Engineering-related disciplines;
At least one years’ relevant working experience;
Experience including CSD/CBWD coordination, AutoCAD drawing, utilities liaison and project management are essential;
Good technical knowledge in Building Services (plumbing field);
Proficient in English and Chinese;
Good communication & interpersonal skills and proactive personality are preferred;
Able to work independently with good problem-solving skills.

 Benefits

Salary: Negotiation;
5.5 Working days;
Bank holiday;
Team gathering.

Please apply by clicking “APPLY NOW” with full resume, current & expected salary and available date to report duty.

